title: Can Facebook Get Past the Antitrust Debacle When It Reports Earnings?
text: After recent reports of a record-setting fine, it needs to put its history of consumer privacy issues behind it.

title: Meet Morgan Beller, the 26-year-old woman behind Facebook's plan to make its own currency
text: Facebook Vice President David Marcus is the face of the company's Libra digital currency, but the original driving force was a 26-year-old female engineer named Morgan Beller.

title: Facebook Turns A $5 Billion Fine And Brutal Congressional Hearings Into A Win
text: Facebook is rumored to have recently reached a $5 billion settlement fine with the Federal Trade Commission for a variety of consumer and privacy practices.
